{
  "texts": [
    "Here, we adopt the perspective of Agency as defined in Bandura (2001)'s social cognitive theory.",
    "Bandura (2001) 's work highlights four features through which humans exercise Agency -Intentionality, Motivation, Self-Efficacy, and Self-Regulation.",
    "Here, we adapt and synthesize these features based on how they may manifest in dialogue.",
    "We take a top-down approach, starting with their higher-level definitions and iteratively refining the definitions and their possible levels (e.g., how strongly or weakly they are expressed) in the context of dialogue.",
    "Intentionality."
  ]
}